---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Jeffery Zhang and the purpose of Doriath."
>
  <section class="page-hero panel narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Jeffery Zhang</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This site is set up as a personal publishing system: a small, fast, static home for
      essays, changelogs, and project notes that should not disappear into a feed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel prose narrow">
    <p>
      Doriath is intentionally simple. Source-authored Astro pages handle the high-signal
      parts of the site, while Markdown content collections keep blog posts close to the
      repository. That makes the whole site easy to edit, review, and deploy.
    </p>
    <p>
      Replace this copy with your own biography, current work, interests, and contact
      details. The structure is already in place, so future updates can stay focused on
      content rather than scaffolding.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

